description: Rock & roll superstar Kenny Winker is coming to China, IL and giving away one ticket to hang out with him on his tour bus, The Garden of Hedon.
title: Kenny Winker Rules

description: After both Frank and Steve sustain life-threatening injuries during a wrestling match, Dr. Falgot performs surgery on them turning Frankensteve into a super brother.
title: Frankensteve

description: Frank bets everyone in town a plate of cheese-sticks that he'll be the focus of the local news program's newest segment: Person of the Day.
title: China-Man Begins

description: Frank discovers that Thomas Jefferson's mythical Diamond Castle is real.
title: The Diamond Castle

description: Steve, Frank & Baby Cakes start a band in order to finally get the attention of the most beautiful celebrity in the world.
title: Charlize

description: In this one-hour musical episode, Baby Cakes wants a magical pet; Frank discovers why women find him unattractive; and Pony & Steve do horrifying things to prove to each other that they are good people.
title: Magical Pet

description: Steve's dislike of The Beach Boys goes well beyond their music.
title: Surfer God

description: Baby Cakes brings a date to the University's "Faculty Prom," which is held at the old, abandoned schoolhouse full of surprisingly vicious inhabitants.
title: Prom Face/Off

description: After The Dean raises tuition to 500 grand a semester, Pony must go to drastic measures in order to stay in school.
title: Is College Worth It?

description: Ronald Reagan returns to China, IL to exact revenge on Steve, who  years earlier impersonated the former president in a kid's talent show on live TV.
title: Rewind, Pause, Play

description: Student registration for the History Department sinks to an all-time low after the death of Harold, one of the faculty's best professors.  Steve must come up with a plan to save their jobs while Frank becomes convinced that he's getting unsolicited attention from a paranormal being.
title: Coming out of the Casket

description: When all of the students on campus fail their finals on Christmas, the professors must come up with a plan to re-teach them everything before New Years, or risk losing their jobs.
title: Chinese New Year

description: The campus becomes victim to an infestation of wild hogs.
title: Wild Hogs

description: Baby Cakes misunderstands a lecture on Senator Joe McCarthy's infamous "Witch Hunts."
title: Prank Week

description: After Steve hires another history professor who coincidentally looks just like him, he immediately regrets his decision.

input: Do You Know Who You Look Like?
You Know Who You Look Like?

title: Do You Know Who You Look Like?

description: Crows have the intelligence of 4-year old humans, so The Dean enrolls a murder of them at UCI as new students.
title: Crow College

description: Steve, Frank, Pony & Baby Cakes become life coaches for each other.
title: Life Coaches

description: It's the first day of school and Frank is determined to give the perfect lecture.
title: The Perfect Lecture

description: It's Parent's Day at UCI (for faculty, not students), but Baby Cakes can't attend because he has to visit his mom for the weekend.
title: Parent's Day

description: Frank's anus learns to speak, and quickly becomes a world-famous stand-up comedian.
title: Best Face Forward

description: Baby Cakes' imaginary ex-best friend used to haunt Baby Cakes' dreams, but now with Facebook he's found a way of haunting his reality.
title: Dream Reamer

description: After the Dean loses control of the school to his arch-rival, Steve, Pony & Baby Cakes must help him regain the physical and psychological strength to take it back.
title: Dean vs. Mayor

description: Total Validation, China IL's newest counseling service, will determine who is right or wrong in any relationship.
title: Total Validation

description: Steve and Baby Cakes strike it rich, while Frank falls in love with a piece of a movie star.
title: Gummie World

description: The Mayor bans eating anchovies in China, IL, while Trump’s Kid joins UCI as its newest student.
title: Bi-Topping-Ality

description: Steve realizes life after tenure isn't as exciting as he suspected, and Pony finds out that the Dean has a secret that he'd do anything to keep hidden.
title: Secret Society

description: Frank proves his masculinity by challenging a boxing legend to a fight, while Baby Cakes and Pony battle in a game of Dungeons and Dragons.
title: Displays of Manhood

description: Different departments on campus are selected for The Dean's List, an annual scavenger hunt that is much more dangerous than it sounds.
title: Dean's List

description: After a giant baby is born in the Super Science lab, obliterating the campus, the faculty is split between whether they should raise the monstrous infant or destroy it.
title: Baby Boom

description: Frank and Steve compete over their annual "Gentleman's Bet"; The Dean & The Mayor solicit Pony & Baby Cakes’ help for a Think Tank.
title: A Gentleman's Bet
